Aero Lloyd.label: Aero Lloyd
Aero Lloyd.description:
Aero Lloyd Flugreisen GmbH & Co, operated as Aero Lloyd, was a German charter airline based in Oberursel, Germany.
It was originally headquartered in Frankfurt before it was moved to Oberursel. Wikipedia

Aer Arann.label: Aer Arann
Aer Arann.description: Aer Arann is a regional airline based in Dublin, Ireland. The airline operates scheduled services on behalf of Aer Lingus Regional. The airline has three bases in Cork, Dublin and Shannon which operate under the Aer Lingus Regional brand. Wikipedia

Afriqiyah Airways.label: Afriqiyah Airways
Afriqiyah Airways.description: Afriqiyah Airways is a state-owned airline based in Tripoli, Libya. Before the Libyan civil war of 2011 it operated domestic services between Tripoli and Benghazi, and international scheduled services ... Wikipedia

Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela.label: Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela
Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela.description: Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela, normally referred to as just Aeropostal, is a formerly state-owned airline of Venezuela based in Torre Polar Oeste in Caracas, Venezuela. It operates domestic services and international services in the Caribbean. Wikipedia

AirBaltic.label: airBaltic
AirBaltic.description: A/S Air Baltic Corporation, operating as AirBaltic and styled as airBaltic, is the Latvian flag carrier airline and a low-cost carrier, with its head office on the grounds of Riga International Airport in Mārupe municipality, near the capital, Riga. Wikipedia

Air – Transport Europe.label: Air – Transport Europe
Air – Transport Europe.description: Air-Transport Europe spol. s r.o. is a specialist Slovakian airline based in Poprad. Using a business jet and a helicopter fleet, it undertakes personal transport, emergency medical services, aerial works and contract helicopter services. Wikipedia

Afrinat International Airlines.label: Afrinat International Airlines
Afrinat International Airlines.description: Afrinat International Airlines was an airline headquartered in Bakau, the Gambia. It was founded in 2002, and provided scheduled services within West Africa out of Banjul International Airport. In 2004, the airline ceased to exist. Wikipedia

Air Bremen.label: Air Bremen
Air Bremen.description: Air Bremen was a small German airline based in Bremen operating between 1988 and 1990. Wikipedia

Air Arabia.label: Air Arabia
Air Arabia.description: Air Arabia is a low-cost airline with its head office in the Sharjah Freight Center, Sharjah International Airport, in Sharjah, United Arab Emirates. Wikipedia

Air Botswana.label: Air Botswana
Air Botswana.description: Air Botswana Corporation is the state-owned national airline of Botswana. It operates scheduled domestic and regional flights from its main base at Sir Seretse Khama International Airport in Gaborone, where it has its head office. Wikipedia

Air Cairo.label: Air Cairo
Air Cairo.description: Air Cairo is a low fare airline based in Cairo, Egypt. The airline is the low fare subsidiary of EgyptAir which operates scheduled flights to the middle east, and inclusive tour flights to Egypt from Europe, Africa and Asia. Wikipedia

Air Caraïbes.label: Air Caraïbes
Air Caraïbes.description: Air Caraïbes is a French airline and is the regional airline of the French Caribbean which comprises two overseas departments of France Guadeloupe and Martinique. The airline is headquartered in Les Abymes in Guadeloupe. Wikipedia

Air Europe.label: Air Europa
Air Europe.description: Air Europa Líneas Aéreas, S.A.U. is the third largest airline in Spain after Iberia and Vueling. The airline is headquartered in the Polígono Son Noguera in the Centro Empresarial Globalia in Llucmajor, Majorca, Spain. Wikipedia

Air Dolomiti.label: Air Dolomiti
Air Dolomiti.description: Air Dolomiti S.p.A. Linee Aeree Regionali Europee is an Italian regional airline with its head office in Dossobuono, Villafranca di Verona, Italy. Wikipedia

Air Koryo.label: Air Koryo
Air Koryo.description: Air Koryo is the state-owned national flag carrier airline of North Korea, headquartered in Sunan-guyŏk, Pyongyang. Wikipedia

Air Inter.label: Air Inter
Air Inter.description: Air Inter was a semi-public French domestic airline. Before its merger with Air France, the airline was headquartered in Paray-Vieille-Poste, Essonne. Earlier in its life, it was headquartered in the 1st arrondissement of Paris. Wikipedia

Air Mandalay.label: Air Mandalay
Air Mandalay.description: Air Mandalay is an airline based in Yangon, Myanmar. It is a regional airline operating domestic services and international charter flights to neighboring countries. Its main base is Yangon International Airport. Wikipedia

Air Malawi.label: Air Malawi
Air Malawi.description: Air Malawi Limited was the state-owned national airline of Malawi, based in Blantyre, which operated regional passenger services. Wikipedia

Air Uganda.label: Air Uganda
Air Uganda.description: Meridiana Africa Airlines Limited, trading as Air Uganda, is a privately owned airline founded in 2007 in Uganda. Wikipedia

Air Mekong.label: Air Mekong
Air Mekong.description: Mekong Aviation Joint Stock Company, doing business as Air Mekong, was an airline from Vietnam which operated scheduled passenger flights from its base at Phu Quoc Airport and secondary hubs at Noi Bai ... Wikipedia

Air Slovakia.label: Air Slovakia
Air Slovakia.description: Air Slovakia was an airline based in Bratislava, Slovakia, operating out of M. R. Štefánik Airport. The airline offered scheduled and chartered passenger flights, as well as aircraft lease. Wikipedia

Air Zimbabwe.label: Air Zimbabwe
Air Zimbabwe.description: Air Zimbabwe is the national airline of Zimbabwe, headquartered on the property of Harare International Airport, in Harare. Wikipedia

Amerer Air.label: Amerer Air
Amerer Air.description: Amerer Air is/was a cargo airline based in Linz, Austria. It is Austria's largest dedicated cargo airline operating services from Linz and Cologne throughout Europe, the Middle East and North Africa. Its main base is Linz Airport. Wikipedia

Atlas Air.label: Atlas Air
Atlas Air.description: Atlas Air, Inc., is an American cargo and passenger charter airline based in Purchase, Harrison, New York. It operates scheduled freight flights on a wet lease basis for some of the world's leading airlines, flying to 101 cities in 46 countries. Wikipedia

American Overseas Airlines.label: American Overseas Airlines
American Overseas Airlines.description: American Overseas Airlines was an airline that operated between the United States and Europe between 1945 and 1950. It was headquartered in Midtown Manhattan, New York City. Wikipedia

Astar Air Cargo.label: Astar Air Cargo
Astar Air Cargo.description: ASTAR Air Cargo was an American cargo airline based in Miami, Florida, USA. It operated regularly scheduled cargo charter services to as many as 34 US airports and nine international airports on behalf ... Wikipedia

Atlas Blue.label: Atlas Blue
Atlas Blue.description: Atlas Blue was a low-cost airline with its head office on the grounds of Marrakech-Menara Airport in Marrakech, Morocco, operating out of Menara International Airport. Wikipedia

Austral Líneas Aéreas.label: Austral Líneas Aéreas
Austral Líneas Aéreas.description: Cielos del Sur S.A., operating as Austral Líneas Aéreas, more commonly known by its shortened name Austral, is a domestic airline of Argentina, the sister company of Aerolíneas Argentinas. Wikipedia

Baboo (airline).label: Baboo
Baboo (airline).description: Fly Baboo SA, marketed as Baboo, was a regional airline based on the grounds of Geneva International Airport and in Grand-Saconnex, Switzerland. Wikipedia

Bahamasair.label: Bahamasair
Bahamasair.description: Bahamasair Holdings Limited, operating as Bahamasair, is an airline based in the Bahamasair House in Nassau, Bahamas. Wikipedia

Berlin European UK.label: Berlin European UK
Berlin European UK.description: Berlin European UK is a defunct regional UK airline based at Tegel Airport in what used to be West Berlin in the days prior to Germany's [re-]unification. Wikipedia

Aloha Airlines.label: Aloha Airlines
Aloha Airlines.description: Aloha Airlines was an American airline headquartered in Honolulu, Oahu, Hawaii, operating from a hub at Honolulu International Airport. Operations began on July 26, 1946, and ceased on March 31, 2008. Wikipedia

Bangkok Airways.label: Bangkok Airways
Bangkok Airways.description: Bangkok Airways Public Company Limited is a regional airline based in Vibhavadi Rangsit Road, Chatuchak District, Bangkok, Thailand. Wikipedia

Birgenair.label: Birgenair
Birgenair.description: Birgenair was a Turkish charter airline company established in 1988 with headquarters in Istanbul, Turkey. Wikipedia

Buddha Air.label: Buddha Air
Buddha Air.description: Buddha Air Pvt. Ltd is an airline based in Jawalakhel, Lalitpur District, Nepal, near Patan. It operates domestic as well as international services within Nepal and India, serving mainly large towns ... Wikipedia

Braathens.label: Braathens
Braathens.description: Braathens ASA, until 1997 Braathens South American & Far East Airtransport A/S and trading as Braathens SAFE, was a Norwegian airline which operated from 1946 until it merged with Scandinavian Airlines Norway in 2004 to become SAS Braathens. Wikipedia

Bulgarian Air Charter.label: Bulgarian Air Charter
Bulgarian Air Charter.description: Bulgarian Air Charter is a charter airline based in Sofia, Bulgaria. It operates charter services for tour operators between the two Bulgarian Black Sea airports Burgas Airport and Varna Airport; and ... Wikipedia

CAL Cargo Air Lines.label: CAL Cargo Air Lines
CAL Cargo Air Lines.description: CAL Cargo Air Lines Ltd. is a cargo airline with its corporate headquarters in the Airport City development of Ben Gurion International Airport, Israel. Wikipedia

Central Connect Airlines.label: Central Connect Airlines
Central Connect Airlines.description: Central Connect Airlines is an airline based in Ostrava, Czech Republic. It operates leasing and charter services. Its main base is Leoš Janáček Airport Ostrava. Wikipedia

Contact Air.label: Contact Air
Contact Air.description: Contact Air Flugdienst was a German regional airline from Stuttgart. Based at Stuttgart Airport, it operated scheduled passenger flights under the Lufthansa Regional brand. Wikipedia

Chalk's International Airlines.label: Chalk's International Airlines
Chalk's International Airlines.description: Chalk's International Airlines, formerly Chalk's Ocean Airways, was an airline with its headquarters on the grounds of Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport in unincorporated Broward County, Florida near Fort Lauderdale. Wikipedia

Cosmic Air.label: Cosmic Air
Cosmic Air.description: Cosmic Air was an airline based in Kathmandu, Nepal. It operated scheduled domestic and international services out of Kathmandu Airport, aiming at foreign tourists. Wikipedia

Corsair International.label: Corsair International
Corsair International.description: Corsair S.A. trading as Corsair International, is an airline based in Rungis, France. It is the second largest French airline after Air France and operates international scheduled and charter services ... Wikipedia

Carpatair.label: Carpatair
Carpatair.description:
S.C. Carpatair S.A. is a Romanian regional airline based in Ghiroda, Timis County, near Timişoara.
Founded in 1999, Carpatair is 100% privately owned with the majority of shareholders being Swiss. Wikipedia

Cronus Airlines.label: Cronus Airlines
Cronus Airlines.description: Cronus Airlines was a Greek airline based in Athens. It operated scheduled as well as chartered flights using a fleet of Boeing 737-300 & 400 aircraft. Wikipedia

Eurowings.label: Eurowings
Eurowings.description: 'Eurowings Luftverkehrs AG', part of Lufthansa Regional, the Lufthansa Group and the Star Alliance is a regional airline with its head office in the Düsseldorf Administrative Center in Düsseldorf, Germany. Wikipedia

First Choice Airways.label: First Choice Airways
First Choice Airways.description: First Choice Airways was a British charter airline of European tour operator TUI Travel PLC, based in Crawley, England. It flew to more than 60 destinations worldwide from 14 UK and Irish airports. Wikipedia

FlyNordic.label: FlyNordic
FlyNordic.description: FlyNordic was an airline based in Stockholm, Sweden. It operated scheduled and charter services in Scandinavia and Europe. Its main base was Stockholm-Arlanda Airport, Stockholm. Wikipedia

Germania (airline).label: Germania
Germania (airline).description: Germania Fluggesellschaft mbH, operating as Germania, is a privately owned German airline with its headquarters in Berlin. Germania operates scheduled and chartered flights and aircraft lease services. Wikipedia

Flyglobespan.label: Flyglobespan
Flyglobespan.description: Flyglobespan was a British low-cost airline based in Edinburgh, Scotland. It formerly operated scheduled services from five airports across the UK and Ireland to destinations in Europe, North America, North Africa and South Africa. Wikipedia

Ghana International Airlines.label: Ghana International Airlines
Ghana International Airlines.description:
Ghana International Airlines was the national airline of the Republic of Ghana. The airline suspended operations on 13 May 2010.
GIA operated scheduled and charter passenger and cargo services. Its main base was Kotoka International Airport, Accra. Wikipedia

Hemus Air.label: Hemus Air
Hemus Air.description: Hemus Air was an airline based in Sofia, Bulgaria. It operated scheduled domestic and international services from Sofia and Varna, as well as charter, cargo and air ambulance services. Its main base was Sofia Airport, with a hub at Varna Airport. Wikipedia

Icelandair.label: Icelandair
Icelandair.description: Icelandair is the main airline of Iceland, headquartered at Reykjavík Airport in Reykjavík. It is part of the Icelandair Group and currently operates scheduled services to 35 cities in 16 countries on ... Wikipedia

Kalitta Air.label: Kalitta Air
Kalitta Air.description: Kalitta Air is an American cargo airline headquartered in Ypsilanti Township, Michigan. It operates international scheduled and ad-hoc cargo charter services. Its main base is Willow Run Airport near Ypsilanti. Wikipedia

Interflug.label: Interflug
Interflug.description: Interflug GmbH was the national airline of East Germany from 1963 to 1990. Based in East Berlin, it operated scheduled and chartered flights to European and intercontinental destinations out of its hub ... Wikipedia

Karat (airline).label: Karat
Karat (airline).description: Karat was an airline based in Moscow, Russia. It operates scheduled services from Moscow and charter flights from Kazan, as well as VIP and business aviation services. Wikipedia

Grossmann Jet Service.label: Grossmann Jet Service
Grossmann Jet Service.description: Grossmann Jet Service spol. s r.o. is a private jet operator based in Prague, Czech Republic. The company provides executive charter services, as well as aircraft management and brokerage. Its main base is Vaclav Havel Airport, Prague., Wikipedia

Lauda Air.label: Lauda Air
Lauda Air.description: Lauda Air Luftfahrt GmbH was an airline headquartered at Vienna International Airport in Schwechat, Austria. It was owned by Niki Lauda for much of its history. Wikipedia

Korean Air.label: Korean Air
Korean Air.description: Korean Air Lines Co., Ltd., operating as Korean Air, is both the flag carrier and the largest airline of South Korea, with global headquarters located in Gonghang-dong, Gangseo-gu, Seoul, South Korea. Wikipedia

Kulula.com.label: kulula.com
Kulula.com.description: kulula.com, sometimes simply known as kulula, is a South African no-frills airline, operating on major domestic routes out of OR Tambo International Airport and Lanseria International Airport, both just outside of Johannesburg. Wikipedia

Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano.label: Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano
Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano.description: Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano S.A.M., abbreviated LAB, also known as LAB Airlines, was an airline serving as flag carrier of Bolivia. It operated domestic and international flights, aiming at passenger as well as cargo transport. Wikipedia

Lufthansa Cargo.label: Lufthansa Cargo
Lufthansa Cargo.description: Lufthansa Cargo AG is a cargo airline from Germany, operating worldwide air freight and logistics services on behalf of Lufthansa, of which it is a wholly owned subsidiary. Wikipedia

Martinair.label: Martinair
Martinair.description: Martinair Holland N.V., operating as Martinair, is a Dutch airline based in Amsterdam, The Netherlands. The airline was founded in 1958 by Martin Schröder. Wikipedia

Maersk Air.label: Maersk Air
Maersk Air.description: Maersk Air was a Danish airline, based in Dragør, Dragør Municipality; Maersk was part of the A.P. Moller-Maersk Group. Wikipedia

Mahan Air.label: Mahan Air
Mahan Air.description: Mahan Airlines, operating under the name Mahan Air is a private airline based in Tehran, Iran. It operates scheduled domestic services and international flights to the Far East, Middle East, Central Asia, and Europe. Wikipedia

Mexicana de Aviación.label: Mexicana de Aviación
Mexicana de Aviación.description: Founded in 1921, Compañía Mexicana de Aviación, S.A. de C.V. was Mexico's oldest airline and one of the oldest continuously single-branded airlines before ceasing operations on August 28, 2010. Wikipedia

Nouvelair.label: Nouvelair
Nouvelair.description: Nouvelair Limited Company is a Tunisian airline with its registered office in Tunis, while its head office in the Dhkila Tourist Zone in Monastir, near the Hôtel Sahara Beach. Wikipedia

Montenegro Airlines.label: Montenegro Airlines
Montenegro Airlines.description: Montenegro Airlines a.d., operating as Montenegro Airlines, is the flag carrier of Montenegro, headquartered in Podgorica. The company is currently completely state-owned and enjoys financial and protectionist support from the government. Wikipedia

Nepal Airlines.label: Nepal Airlines
Nepal Airlines.description: Nepal Airlines is the flag carrier airline of Nepal. Its head office is in the NAC Building in Kathmandu, and its main base is Tribhuvan International Airport, Kathmandu. The airline was established in July 1958 as Royal Nepal Airlines Corporation. Wikipedia

Pacific Southwest Airlines.label: Pacific Southwest Airlines
Pacific Southwest Airlines.description: Pacific Southwest Airlines was a United States airline headquartered in San Diego, California that operated from 1949 to 1988. It was one of the first large discount airlines in the United States. Wikipedia

People Express Airlines.label: People Express Airlines
People Express Airlines.description: People Express Airlines, stylized as PEOPLExpress, also known as People Express Travel, was an American low-cost airline that operated from 1981 to 1987, when they merged into Continental Airlines. Wikipedia

SkyEurope.label: SkyEurope
SkyEurope.description: SkyEurope Airlines was a low-cost airline headquartered in Bratislava, with its main base at M. R. Štefánik Airport in Bratislava, Slovakia, and another base in Prague. Wikipedia

S7 Airlines.label: S7 Airlines
S7 Airlines.description: OJSC Siberia Airlines, operating as S7 Airlines, is an airline headquartered in Novosibirsk Oblast, Russia, with offices in Moscow. As of 2008 it was Russia's biggest airline, based on number of domestic passengers. Wikipedia

Phuket Air.label: Phuket Air
Phuket Air.description: Phuket Air is an airline based in Bangkok, Thailand. The airline currently specialises in leasing its fleet of Boeing 747 and 737 aircraft on an ACMI as well as wet lease basis to airlines worldwide needing extra passenger capacity. Wikipedia

SmartWings.label: SmartWings
SmartWings.description: Smart Wings is a low-cost brand of Travel Service Airlines with its head office on the property of Václav Havel Airport Prague in Ruzyně, 6th district, Prague, Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Sterling Airlines.label: Sterling Airlines
Sterling Airlines.description: Sterling Airlines A/S was a low-cost airline with its head office at Copenhagen Airport South in Dragør, Dragør Municipality, Denmark. Wikipedia

SunExpress.label: SunExpress
SunExpress.description: Güneş Ekspress Havacılık A.Ş., doing business as SunExpress, is a Turkish airline based in Antalya, Turkey. It operates scheduled and chartered passenger flights to various destinations in Europe, Asia and North Africa. Wikipedia

Sky Airlines.label: Sky Airline
Sky Airlines.description: Sky Airline is an airline based at Comodoro Arturo Merino Benítez International Airport in Santiago, Chile. It is the second largest airline in the country behind rival LAN Airlines. Wikipedia

Syrian Air.label: Syrian Air
Syrian Air.description: Syrian Arab Airlines, operating as SyrianAir, is the flag carrier airline of Syria. It operates scheduled international services to several destinations in Asia, Europe and North Africa, the number of ... Wikipedia

Transaero Airlines.label: Transaero Airlines
Transaero Airlines.description: OJSC Transaero Airlines or simply Transaero is an airline with its head office on the grounds of Domodedovo International Airport, Domodedovsky District, Moscow Oblast, Russia. Wikipedia

Skyservice.label: Skyservice
Skyservice.description: Skyservice Airlines Inc. was a charter airline based in the Etobicoke area of Toronto, Ontario, Canada. It employed more than 2000 people. Skyservice Airlines Inc. flew within Canada and to the U.S., Caribbean, Mexico, Israel and Europe. Wikipedia

Van Air Europe.label: Van Air Europe
Van Air Europe.description: Van Air Europe is a Czech charter airline, based in Brno, Czech Republic. The airline operates flights on behalf of Citywing using their fleet of four Let L-410 Turbolet aircraft. Wikipedia

Volareweb.com.label: Volareweb.com
Volareweb.com.description: Volare S.p.A., as Volareweb.com, was a low cost subsidiary of the old Alitalia-LAI. Its head office was located in Area Tecnica Sud of Terminal 1 of Milan-Malpensa International Airport, in Ferno, ... Wikipedia

Aegean Airlines.label: Aegean Airlines
Aegean Airlines.description: Aegean Airlines SA is the largest Greek airline by total number of passengers carried, by number of destinations served and by fleet size. Wikipedia

Western Airlines.label: Western Airlines
Western Airlines.description: Western Airlines was a large airline based in California, with operations throughout the western United States and western Canada, as well as into Mexico. Wikipedia

Aer Lingus.label: Aer Lingus
Aer Lingus.description: Aer Lingus Group Plc is the national flag carrier of Ireland. It operates a fleet of mostly Airbus aircraft serving Europe, North Africa, Turkey and the USA. Wikipedia

Welcome Air.label: Welcome Air
Welcome Air.description: Welcome Air Luftfahrt GmbH & Co KG - short Welcome Air - is an airline with its head office in Innsbruck, Austria. Wikipedia

Air Astana.label: Air Astana
Air Astana.description: Air Astana is the principal airline and the flag carrier of the Republic of Kazakhstan, based in Almaty, Kazakhstan. Wikipedia

Aerosvit Airlines.label: Aerosvit Airlines
Aerosvit Airlines.description: AeroSvit Airlines private stock company, operating as AeroSvit — Ukrainian Airlines / АероСвіт, was a Ukrainian private airline. Its head office was on the grounds of the Boryspil International Airport in Boryspil. Wikipedia

Air Canada.label: Air Canada
Air Canada.description: Air Canada is the flag carrier and largest airline of Canada. The airline, founded in 1936, provides scheduled and charter air transport for passengers and cargo to 178 destinations worldwide. Wikipedia

Air Berlin.label: Air Berlin
Air Berlin.description: Air Berlin PLC & Co. Luftverkehrs KG is Germany's second largest airline, after Lufthansa, and Europe's seventh largest airline in terms of passengers carried. Wikipedia

Air China.label: Air China
Air China.description:
Air China Limited is the flag carrier and one of the major airlines of the People's Republic of China, with its headquarters in Shunyi District, Beijing.
Air China's flight operations are based out of Beijing Capital International Airport. Wikipedia

Blue Wings.label: Blue Wing Airlines
Blue Wings.description: Blue Wing Airlines n.v. is an airline with its head office on the grounds of Zorg en Hoop Airport in Paramaribo, Suriname. Wikipedia
